I recently got the comprehensive tests done for self and my wife and the overall experience was quite satisfactory, from booking to collection to delivery of reports on the same day. However, I still have few queries and suggestions for Healthian‚Ä¶
1. If one call the number to book for the test, the executives try to oversell some additional tests always which one has not planned initially and the same happens when the executive comes to collect one‚Äôs sample. It appears as if one is being trapped and gives suspicion on company‚Äôs intentions.
2. The biggest suggestion I have is that it‚Äôs been almost eight years of existence for Healthian however their average ratings is still less than 4, when they claim that they are the best and better than others in every respect. I strongly suggest that they should ideally have a rating of atleast 4.5 which they should achieve within this year, else it certainly gives a bad impression on their credibility and customers can switch to any other service provider, there are plenty of credible names now in the market.
3. Lastly, the quality of the post test consultation given, be it from a dietician or a doctor, should improve. Today, it is average and  run of the mill with little depth and more to do a tick in the box

name: Healthians
review_text:
Fake testing of blood samples

In the garb of deep discounting, Healthians are engaging clintile for blood sample testing in the most fictitious and fake manner. Many of my blood parameters when reported abnormally higher than the normal range, I got my blood sample retested at local reputed lab and to my utter surprise, 7 of them, related with lipid profile, kidney functioning, sodium & phosphorus contents were found wrongly and arbitarily reported by Healthians lab test report dated 26th May, 2022.

When escalated the issue, their Lab Quality team attributed the error to randomness error in any machine. I wondered how different machines shown randomness error on the same day, for the same sample and in the same direction ( upside) ! When rebutted them with this observation, they have opted not to revert back even after lapse of more than 15 days of reporting the issue.

It compels me to conclude that putting some arbitrary numbers against test results is their business model either to cut costs or keeping client engaged for repetitive tests or both.

Went through ordeal for around 5 days till my doctor nephrologist cleared me of any kidney disease after my 2nd test reports and examining me clinically.

Beware of lab test reports from Healthians as these have hardly a sanctity left.
owner_answer: Hi Harpreet, we are concerned to hear it. If you could share the booking details, our team will look into the issue and try to resolve it as soon as possible.

review_text:
-Location Noida
- Usual tests like CBC, vitamins, Sugar, Liver, Kidney, thyroid, etc is what I usually book for my parents and me, and the results look quite accurate compared to what we feel from within.
- Using since 3 years for whole family.
-Home sample pickup facility is good and 95% of the time they are right on clock.
- Reports are provided within 12-24hrs almost always.
- Format of reports is very nice and easily readable. Also gives an overall health score in full body tests.
- Price is very competitive and reasonable compared to private labs that doctors usually recommend.
- Doctors consultation via call are the icing on cake. It's very detailed and helps a lot. You can also call them back.
- One thing to consider as feedback is to perhaps train the sample collection folks better as once in a while there are guys who are slightly new and inexperienced.

review_text: Credibility of Healthian report and test is doubtful. My Liver function test readings from Healthians varied drastically in 1 day. My SGOT level was reported 148 which implies Liver damage as normal range is max upto 34. I have no liver problem and in routine test 3 months ago from Healthians itself my SGOT level was 28. When I raised issue with Healthian doctor as I got concerned he got my LFT and LIPID retest  done next DAY. Now SGOT reading was 67 against 148 previous day. Cholestrol levels also changed next day. I had no change in diet, activity or fasting time. No proper reasoning was given from Healthian physician for such drastic change in readings. But am seriously doubtful with the Healthian lab readings. Better go for some credible labs as in routine cases one can ignore but for serious issues cannot trust these cheap package tests.
